Andrew Marchand and John Ourand break down Troy Aikman’s move from Fox to ESPN for a record-setting five-year, $90-plus million deal. They look at Joe Buck, Fox and ESPN’s decisions. What the next moves could mean for Al Michaels and Amazon. Plus, Amazon’s interest in Kirk Herbstreit and their willingness to approach $100 million for Sean McVay. They also go into MLB’s pending deals with Apple and NBC when games resume. Plus, Sunday Ticket, Turner/US Soccer and a proper sendoff for Post MLB columnist Ken Davidoff.